# JSON Parser

A fast, zero-dependency JSON viewer that runs entirely in the browser.

## Features

- **Syntax-highlighted tree view** — keys, strings, numbers, booleans, and nulls each styled distinctly
- **Live validation** — parses automatically 600 ms after you stop typing; error bar shows the exact parse message
- **Collapsible nodes** — click the arrow on any object or array to collapse it; inline preview shows `…}`
- **Expand / Collapse All** — one-click flatten or fold the entire tree
- **Search** — filters and highlights matching keys or values, auto-expanding ancestor nodes
- **Path breadcrumb** — hover any node to see its full dot-notation path (`$.user.metadata.preferences`)
- **Copy values** — hover a node to reveal a copy button; copies the value (or pretty-printed JSON for objects/arrays)
- **Stats bar** — total keys, max depth, object count, array count, and input size
- **Line numbers** — in both the input editor and the tree; toggleable via the `# Lines` button
- **Resizable split pane** — drag the divider between input and tree panels
- **Sample data** — click `⚡ Sample` to load a representative JSON object

## Usage

Open `index.html` directly in any modern browser — no server or build step required.

```
Json Parser/
├── index.html   # markup and layout
├── styles.css   # all visual styles and CSS variables
├── app.js       # parsing, tree rendering, and UI logic
└── README.md
```

## Keyboard / interaction quick-reference

| Action | How |
|---|---|
| Parse | Click **▶ Parse** or wait 600 ms after typing |
| Load sample | Click **⚡ Sample** |
| Clear | Click **✕ Clear** |
| Toggle line numbers | Click **# Lines** |
| Collapse a node | Click the **▸** arrow on any object / array |
| Expand a node | Click the **▾** arrow |
| Expand all | Click **⊞ Expand All** |
| Collapse all | Click **⊟ Collapse All** |
| Copy entire JSON | Click **⎘ Copy JSON** |
| Copy a single value | Hover a leaf node → click **copy** |
| Search | Type in the search box (top-right of tree panel) |
| Resize panels | Drag the vertical divider |